{
  "stem": "868.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was announced soon after the capitulation on the armistice that, that was signed that refugees from the north would be allowed to go back.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So we left that village in the hope that we would be able to-- because when we left Paris, we abandoned a fully-furnished and equipped three-room apartment.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when we left, we just took a few suitcases, leaving everything behind.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we thought we would get back and retrieve these, these things.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were stopped at the Demarcation Line and-- by the German authorities.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And since we did not have French passports-- we were never given in those three years French citizenship-- we were sent, sent back.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At that time, there were no yet organized anti-Jewish actions or pogroms or raids, arrests.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Just the fact that we did not have French identification papers, we were sent, sent back.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then started, from that time on-- we are now 1940, summer of 1940, fall of 1940-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] going from one place to the other as now [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] anti-Jewish laws were promulgated with certain regularity.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "First you had to register that you were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Then you had to-- certain professions you could not exercise, certain places you couldn't live, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So-- also, arrests started being made in, in, in France of, of Jews.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And to be ahead of the gendarmes, we went from one place to the next, various localities all throughout the South of France.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So one was Lugagnac.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The other one was Limoges.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The third one was Cahors.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The fourth one was Florac.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The fifth one was Lons-le-Saunier.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That's all over the map, this.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Hmm?",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
